var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"location":"benchmarks/#Benchmarks","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Benchmarks","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Liouvillian-Action:-cuDensityMat-GPU-vs-CPU-Sparse","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Liouvillian Action: cuDensityMat GPU vs CPU Sparse","text":"We benchmark a single evaluation of the Lindblad Liouvillian action Lrho for a dual-rail qubit system with M coupled cavities (Fock truncation d=3):\n\ndotrho = -iH rho + gamma sum_m left( a_m rho a_m^dagger - frac12a_m^dagger a_m rho right)","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Results:-NVIDIA-A100-40GB-vs-12-core-CPU","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Results: NVIDIA A100 40GB vs 12-core CPU","text":"Cavities (M) Hilbert dim rho elements cuDensityMat (A100) CPU Sparse GPU Speedup\n2 9 81 0.27 ms 0.001 ms CPU wins\n4 81 6,561 1.2 ms 0.14 ms CPU wins\n6 729 531K 8.1 ms 40 ms 4.9x\n8 6,561 43M 621 ms N/A GPU only option\n9 19,683 387M 6,742 ms N/A GPU only option","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Key-Findings","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Key Findings","text":"Crossover at M=6 (729-dimensional Hilbert space): cuDensityMat on A100 is 4.9x faster than CPU sparse matrix-vector multiply.\nBeyond M=6, CPU is infeasible: the sparse superoperator for M=8 would require >100 GB to construct. cuDensityMat never materializes the superoperator — it uses tensor network contraction.\nGPU overhead dominates at small sizes: for M=2,4, kernel launch overhead (~0.3 ms) exceeds the actual computation time. CPU wins trivially.","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Why-cuDensityMat-Scales-Better","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Why cuDensityMat Scales Better","text":"The CPU sparse approach explicitly constructs the Liouvillian superoperator mathcalL as a D^2 times D^2 sparse matrix (where D = d^M), then computes mathcalL cdot textvec(rho) via SpMV. The memory for the sparse matrix scales as O(M cdot D^2) non-zeros.\n\ncuDensityMat instead decomposes mathcalLrho as a sum of tensor network contractions over the elementary operators. Each contraction involves small tensors (d times d per mode) and the density matrix, never forming the full superoperator. The computational cost scales more favorably with the number of modes M.","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Validation","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Validation","text":"The CPU and GPU implementations produce bitwise-identical results for the static Liouvillian (verified at t=0). For time-dependent simulations with callbacks, diagonal populations agree to machine precision (10^-16), with off-diagonal coherences differing by  10^-3 after 50 RK4 steps due to floating-point operation ordering.","category":"section"},{"location":"benchmarks/#Hardware-Details","page":"Benchmarks","title":"Hardware Details","text":"GPU: NVIDIA A100-SXM4-40GB (2 TB/s bandwidth, 9.7 TFLOPS FP64)\nCPU: 12 vCPUs (GCE a2-highgpu-1g instance, 85 GB RAM)\nBenchmark script: benchmark/run_benchmarks.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"getting-started/#Getting-Started","page":"Getting Started","title":"Getting Started","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"getting-started/#Installation","page":"Getting Started","title":"Installation","text":"CuQuantum.jl requires a CUDA-capable GPU and the NVIDIA cuQuantum SDK (provided automatically via cuQuantum_jll).\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/harmoniqs/CuQuantum.jl\")\n\nnote: GPU Required\nCuQuantum.jl requires a CUDA-capable GPU at runtime. The package will load without a GPU, but all computation functions require one. Supported architectures: Turing (T4), Ampere (A100), Ada (L4/L40), Hopper (H100), Blackwell (B200).","category":"section"},{"location":"getting-started/#Dependencies","page":"Getting Started","title":"Dependencies","text":"CuQuantum.jl depends on:\n\nCUDA.jl — Julia GPU computing\ncuQuantum_jll — prebuilt cuQuantum SDK binaries\nCEnum.jl — C enum support\n\nAll dependencies are installed automatically.","category":"section"},{"location":"getting-started/#Verify-Installation","page":"Getting Started","title":"Verify Installation","text":"using CuQuantum\nusing CuQuantum.CuDensityMat\n\n# Check the cuDensityMat library version\nv = CuDensityMat.version()\nprintln(\"cuDensityMat version: $v\")\n\n# Create and close a workspace (verifies GPU + library connectivity)\nws = WorkStream()\nclose(ws)\nprintln(\"CuQuantum.jl is working!\")","category":"section"},{"location":"getting-started/#Basic-Workflow","page":"Getting Started","title":"Basic Workflow","text":"Every CuQuantum.jl simulation follows this pattern:\n\nCreate a WorkStream — manages the GPU handle, workspace memory, and CUDA stream\nDefine elementary operators — single-mode operators (e.g., annihilation, number, Pauli matrices) uploaded to GPU\nBuild operator terms — tensor products of elementary operators acting on specific modes\nAssemble the composite operator — sum of terms with coefficients and duality flags (left/right of rho)\nPrepare the action — one-time workspace allocation and contraction planning\nCompute — evaluate Lrho at a given time, as many times as needed\nClean up — close the WorkStream\n\nSee the Concepts Overview section for detailed explanations of each step.","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/callbacks/#Time-Dependent-Callbacks","page":"Callbacks","title":"Time-Dependent Callbacks","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/callbacks/#Overview","page":"Callbacks","title":"Overview","text":"Many quantum systems have time-dependent Hamiltonians — control pulses, modulated couplings, or driven transitions. CuQuantum.jl supports this through callback functions that are called by the GPU library at each time step.\n\nThere are two types of callbacks:\n\nScalar callbacks — time-dependent scalar coefficients multiplying an operator term\nTensor callbacks — time-dependent tensor elements of an elementary operator","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/callbacks/#Scalar-Callbacks","page":"Callbacks","title":"Scalar Callbacks","text":"A scalar callback provides a time-dependent complex coefficient c(t theta):\n\n# Define a time-dependent detuning: δ(t) = Δ sin(ωt)\nfunction detuning_callback(time, params, storage)\n    Δ = 2π * 1.0  # detuning amplitude\n    ω = 2π * 0.5  # modulation frequency\n    for b in eachindex(storage)\n        storage[b] = ComplexF64(Δ * sin(ω * time))\n    end\nend\n\n# Wrap it for the C API\ncb, gcb, refs = wrap_scalar_callback(detuning_callback)\n\n# Use in an elementary product\nappend_elementary_product!(term, [elem_n], Int32[0], Int32[0];\n    coefficient=ComplexF64(1.0),\n    coefficient_callback=cb,\n    coefficient_gradient_callback=gcb)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/callbacks/#Callback-Signature","page":"Callbacks","title":"Callback Signature","text":"function my_scalar_callback(\n    time::Float64,           # current simulation time\n    params::Matrix{Float64}, # user parameters, shape (num_params, batch_size)\n    storage::Vector{T}       # output: write coefficients here, length batch_size\n)\n\nThe function must write the coefficient value(s) into storage. For batched simulations, storage has one element per batch member.","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/callbacks/#Tensor-Callbacks","page":"Callbacks","title":"Tensor Callbacks","text":"A tensor callback provides time-dependent matrix elements for an elementary operator:\n\n# Time-dependent rotation matrix: R(t) = [[cos(t), -sin(t)], [sin(t), cos(t)]]\nfunction rotation_callback(time, params, storage)\n    for b in axes(storage, 3)\n        storage[1, 1, b] = complex(cos(time))\n        storage[2, 1, b] = complex(sin(time))\n        storage[1, 2, b] = complex(-sin(time))\n        storage[2, 2, b] = complex(cos(time))\n    end\nend\n\ntensor_cb, tensor_gcb, refs = wrap_tensor_callback(rotation_callback)\n\n# Create elementary operator with time-dependent elements\nelem = create_elementary_operator(ws, [2], static_data;\n    tensor_callback=tensor_cb,\n    tensor_gradient_callback=tensor_gcb)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/callbacks/#Gradient-Callbacks","page":"Callbacks","title":"Gradient Callbacks","text":"For backward differentiation (parameter gradients), provide a gradient function:\n\nfunction my_gradient(time, params, scalar_grad, params_grad)\n    # Compute ∂c/∂t and ∂c/∂θ\n    for b in axes(scalar_grad, 1)\n        scalar_grad[b] = ...  # gradient of coefficient w.r.t. time\n        params_grad[1, b] = ...  # gradient w.r.t. first parameter\n    end\nend\n\ncb, gcb, refs = wrap_scalar_callback(my_coeff; gradient=my_gradient)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/callbacks/#GC-Safety","page":"Callbacks","title":"GC Safety","text":"Callbacks are registered in a global registry to prevent garbage collection while the C library holds raw pointers. Always call unregister_callback!(refs) after destroying the operator that uses the callback:\n\ncb, gcb, refs = wrap_scalar_callback(my_func)\n# ... use cb in operators ...\n# ... destroy operators ...\nunregister_callback!(refs)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/operators/#Operators","page":"Operators","title":"Operators","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/operators/#Operator-Hierarchy","page":"Operators","title":"Operator Hierarchy","text":"CuQuantum.jl follows the cuDensityMat operator hierarchy:","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/operators/#Elementary-Operators","page":"Operators","title":"Elementary Operators","text":"An ElementaryOperator is a tensor acting on one or more modes of the Hilbert space. It can be:\n\nDense — full d times d matrix (e.g., Pauli matrices, annihilation operators)\nMultidiagonal — sparse diagonal structure (e.g., number operators)\n\nElementary operators are uploaded to GPU memory once and reused across many terms.\n\n# Single-mode annihilation operator (d=3 Fock space)\na_data = CUDA.CuVector{ComplexF64}([0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, √2, 0])\nelem_a = create_elementary_operator(ws, [3], a_data)\n\n# Two-mode fused operator for a⊗a† (used in Lindblad sandwich terms)\naa_dag = zeros(ComplexF64, 3, 3, 3, 3)\n# ... fill in tensor elements ...\nelem_fused = create_elementary_operator(ws, [3, 3], CUDA.CuVector{ComplexF64}(vec(aa_dag)))","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/operators/#Operator-Terms","page":"Operators","title":"Operator Terms","text":"An OperatorTerm is a sum of tensor products of elementary operators. Each product specifies:\n\nWhich elementary operators participate\nWhich modes they act on (modes_acted_on)\nWhether each mode acts on the ket (left) or bra (right) side of rho (mode_action_duality)\nA scalar coefficient (static or time-dependent via callback)\n\nterm = create_operator_term(ws, [3, 3])  # 2-mode system\n\n# Append: σ_z on mode 0, ket-side, with coefficient χ\nappend_elementary_product!(term, [elem_σz], Int32[0], Int32[0];\n    coefficient=ComplexF64(χ))\n\nThe mode_action_duality array controls how each index of the elementary operator interacts with the density matrix:\n\n0 — acts on the ket (left) side: O rho\n1 — acts on the bra (right) side: rho O\n\nFor Lindblad sandwich terms a rho a^dagger, use a fused 2-mode elementary operator with mode_action_duality = [0, 1] and modes_acted_on = [m, m] (same physical mode for both).","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/operators/#Operators-2","page":"Operators","title":"Operators","text":"An Operator is a sum of OperatorTerms, each appended with a duality flag and coefficient:\n\noperator = create_operator(ws, dims)\n\n# -i H ρ  (Hamiltonian acts from the left)\nappend_term!(operator, hamiltonian_term; duality=0, coefficient=ComplexF64(0, -1))\n\n# +i ρ H  (Hamiltonian acts from the right)\nappend_term!(operator, hamiltonian_term; duality=1, coefficient=ComplexF64(0, +1))","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/operators/#Operator-Action","page":"Operators","title":"Operator Action","text":"Once assembled, the operator action Lrho is computed in two phases:\n\nprepare_operator_action! — one-time contraction planning and workspace allocation\ncompute_operator_action! — evaluate Lrho at a given time (can be called repeatedly)\n\nprepare_operator_action!(ws, operator, ρ_in, ρ_out)\n\n# Time-stepping loop\nfor t in time_steps\n    initialize_zero!(ρ_out)\n    compute_operator_action!(ws, operator, ρ_in, ρ_out; time=t, batch_size=1)\n    # ... RK4 or other integration ...\nend","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/operators/#Matrix-Operators","page":"Operators","title":"Matrix Operators","text":"For operators that act on the full Hilbert space (not decomposed into tensor products), use MatrixOperator:\n\n# Full d_total × d_total matrix on GPU\nmat_op = create_matrix_operator(ws, dims, full_matrix_gpu)\n\nThese are less efficient than elementary operators for large systems but useful for small systems or pre-computed matrices.","category":"section"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuDensityMat-API-Reference","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuDensityMat API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat","text":"CuDensityMat\n\nJulia bindings for NVIDIA's cuDensityMat library — high-performance density matrix simulation for analog quantum dynamics (Lindblad master equation, time-dependent Hamiltonians, backward differentiation/gradients).\n\nPart of the CuQuantum.jl package.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState","text":"DenseMixedState{T}(ws, hilbert_space_dims; batch_size=1)\n\nMixed state in dense (density-matrix) representation.\n\nArguments\n\nws::WorkStream: Execution context\nhilbert_space_dims::Vector{Int} or Tuple: Local Hilbert space dimensions\nbatch_size::Int=1: Batch dimension\n\nExample\n\nws = WorkStream()\nrho = DenseMixedState{ComplexF64}(ws, (2, 2))\nallocate_storage!(rho)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState","text":"DensePureState{T}(ws, hilbert_space_dims; batch_size=1)\n\nPure state in dense (state-vector) representation.\n\nArguments\n\nws::WorkStream: Execution context\nhilbert_space_dims::Vector{Int} or Tuple: Local Hilbert space dimensions\nbatch_size::Int=1: Batch dimension\n\nExample\n\nws = WorkStream()\npsi = DensePureState{ComplexF64}(ws, (2, 2, 2))\nallocate_storage!(psi)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.ElementaryOperator","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.ElementaryOperator","text":"ElementaryOperator\n\nWraps a cudensitymatElementaryOperator_t handle. Represents a single-mode operator that can be dense or multidiagonal.\n\nCreate via create_elementary_operator or create_elementary_operator_batch.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Expectation","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Expectation","text":"Expectation\n\nWraps a cudensitymatExpectation_t handle for computing expectation values of an operator with respect to a quantum state.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.MatrixOperator","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.MatrixOperator","text":"MatrixOperator\n\nWraps a cudensitymatMatrixOperator_t handle. Represents a full Hilbert-space dense matrix operator stored locally on a single GPU.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator","text":"Operator\n\nWraps a cudensitymatOperator_t handle. A composite operator consisting of multiple OperatorTerms, each with a duality flag and scalar coefficient.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorAction","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorAction","text":"OperatorAction\n\nWraps a cudensitymatOperatorAction_t handle. Computes the action of one or more operators on input states, accumulating into an output state.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorSpectrum","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorSpectrum","text":"OperatorSpectrum\n\nWraps a cudensitymatOperatorSpectrum_t handle for computing eigenvalues and eigenstates of an operator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorTerm","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorTerm","text":"OperatorTerm\n\nWraps a cudensitymatOperatorTerm_t handle. Represents one or more tensor products of elementary operators acting on specified modes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream","text":"WorkStream(; stream=nothing, memory_limit=nothing, device_id=nothing)\n\nA workspace context bundling a CuDensityMat library handle, workspace descriptor, and CUDA stream. All CuDensityMat operations require a WorkStream.\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nstream::Union{Nothing, CUDA.CuStream}: CUDA stream. Uses the default stream if nothing.\nmemory_limit::Union{Nothing, Int}: Maximum workspace memory in bytes. Default is unlimited.\ndevice_id::Union{Nothing, Int}: CUDA device ordinal. Uses current device if nothing.\n\nExamples\n\nws = WorkStream()                          # default stream, current device\nws = WorkStream(stream=CUDA.CuStream())    # explicit stream\nclose(ws)                                  # release resources\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#Base.close-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"Base.close","text":"close(ws::WorkStream)\n\nExplicitly release all resources held by the WorkStream.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#Base.isopen-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"Base.isopen","text":"isopen(ws::WorkStream)\n\nCheck if the WorkStream is still valid (not yet closed/finalized).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat._get_workspace_limit-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, Union{Nothing, Integer}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat._get_workspace_limit","text":"_get_workspace_limit(ws, user_limit) -> Int\n\nReturn the workspace size limit in bytes. If user_limit is nothing, returns ws.memory_limit if set, or 80% of free GPU memory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.allocate_storage!-Union{Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.allocate_storage!","text":"allocate_storage!(state)\n\nAllocate an appropriately sized buffer and attach it to the state.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_elementary_product!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorTerm, AbstractVector{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.ElementaryOperator}, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_elementary_product!","text":"append_elementary_product!(term, elem_operators, modes_acted_on, mode_action_duality;\n    coefficient=1.0+0im, kwargs...)\n\nAppend a tensor product of elementary operators to the term.\n\nArguments\n\nelem_operators: Vector of ElementaryOperators\nmodes_acted_on: Flattened vector of mode indices (0-based) each operator acts on\nmode_action_duality: Per-mode duality flags (0=ket, nonzero=bra) — same length as modes_acted_on\ncoefficient: Static complex scalar coefficient (default: 1.0+0im)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_elementary_product_batch!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorTerm, AbstractVector{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.ElementaryOperator}, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, Integer, CUDA.CuArray{ComplexF64, 1}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_elementary_product_batch!","text":"append_elementary_product_batch!(term, elem_operators, modes_acted_on,\n    mode_action_duality, batch_size, static_coefficients; kwargs...)\n\nAppend a batched tensor product of elementary operators to the term.\n\nArguments\n\nstatic_coefficients: GPU array of ComplexF64 coefficients (length batch_size)\ntotal_coefficients: GPU storage for total coefficients, or nothing\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_matrix_product!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorTerm, AbstractVector{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.MatrixOperator}, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_matrix_product!","text":"append_matrix_product!(term, matrix_operators, conjugations, action_duality;\n    coefficient=1.0+0im, kwargs...)\n\nAppend a product of matrix operators to the term.\n\nArguments\n\nmatrix_operators: Vector of MatrixOperators\nconjugations: Per-operator conjugation flags (0=normal, nonzero=conjugate-transpose)\naction_duality: Per-operator duality flags (0=ket, nonzero=bra)\ncoefficient: Static complex scalar coefficient (default: 1.0+0im)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_term!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorTerm}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_term!","text":"append_term!(operator, term; duality=0, coefficient=1.0+0im, kwargs...)\n\nAppend an operator term to the composite operator.\n\nArguments\n\nduality: 0 for ket-side (default), nonzero for bra-side\ncoefficient: Static complex scalar coefficient (default: 1.0+0im)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_term_batch!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorTerm, Integer, CUDA.CuArray{ComplexF64, 1}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.append_term_batch!","text":"append_term_batch!(operator, term, batch_size, static_coefficients;\n    duality=0, kwargs...)\n\nAppend a batched operator term.\n\nArguments\n\nstatic_coefficients: GPU array of ComplexF64 coefficients (length batch_size)\ntotal_coefficients: GPU storage for total coefficients, or nothing\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.attach_storage!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}, CUDA.CuArray{T, 1}}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.attach_storage!","text":"attach_storage!(state, data::CuVector{T})\n\nAttach a GPU buffer to the state. The buffer must be F-contiguous and match the required storage size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.clone-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}, CUDA.CuArray{T, 1}}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.clone","text":"clone(state, buf::CuVector{T}) -> State\n\nClone a state with a new storage buffer.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.component_storage_size-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.component_storage_size","text":"component_storage_size(state) -> Vector{Int}\n\nStorage size in bytes for each component.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_action!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorAction, AbstractVector{<:CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_action!","text":"compute_action!(ws, action, states_in, state_out;\n    time=0.0, batch_size=0, params=nothing)\n\nExecute the operator action: state_out = sum_i operator_i(states_in[i]).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_expectation!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Expectation, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState, CUDA.CuArray}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_expectation!","text":"compute_expectation!(ws, expectation, state, result;\n    time=0.0, batch_size=1, num_params=0, params=nothing)\n\nCompute expectation value: result = Tr(operator * state).\n\nArguments\n\nresult: GPU array to store the expectation value(s). For complex operators, use CuVector{ComplexF64} of length batch_size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_operator_action!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_operator_action!","text":"compute_operator_action!(ws, operator, state_in, state_out;\n    time=0.0, batch_size=0, params=nothing)\n\nExecute single-operator action: state_out = operator * state_in.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_operator_action_backward!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState, CUDA.CuArray{Float64, 1}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_operator_action_backward!","text":"compute_operator_action_backward!(ws, operator, state_in, state_out_adj,\n    state_in_adj, params_grad; time=0.0, batch_size=0,\n    num_params=0, params=nothing)\n\nCompute backward differentiation of a single-operator action.\n\nComputes ∂L/∂statein (into `stateinadj) and ∂L/∂params (intoparamsgrad) given ∂L/∂state_out (stateoutadj`).\n\nArguments\n\nstate_in: Forward-pass input state\nstate_out_adj: Adjoint of forward-pass output (∂L/∂state_out)\nstate_in_adj: Output — receives ∂L/∂state_in (accumulated, += semantics)\nparams_grad: GPU vector — receives ∂L/∂params (accumulated, += semantics)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_spectrum!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorSpectrum, Integer, AbstractVector{<:CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}, CUDA.CuArray}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.compute_spectrum!","text":"compute_spectrum!(ws, spectrum, num_eigenstates, eigenstates, eigenvalues;\n    time=0.0, batch_size=1, num_params=0, params=nothing) -> tolerances\n\nCompute eigenvalues and eigenstates.\n\nArguments\n\nnum_eigenstates: Number of eigenvalues/eigenstates to compute (≤ max from prepare)\neigenstates: Vector of pre-allocated AbstractStates to receive eigenstates\neigenvalues: GPU array to receive eigenvalues. For Hermitian operators, use CuVector{Float64} of length num_eigenstates * batch_size. For non-Hermitian, use CuVector{ComplexF64}.\n\nReturns\n\ntolerances: Vector{Float64} of convergence tolerances for each eigenvalue\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.configure_spectrum!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorSpectrum, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.cudensitymatOperatorSpectrumConfig_t, Integer}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.configure_spectrum!","text":"configure_spectrum!(ws, spectrum, attribute, value)\n\nConfigure a spectrum solver parameter.\n\nArguments\n\nattribute: One of:\nCUDENSITYMAT_OPERATOR_SPECTRUM_CONFIG_MAX_EXPANSION — max Krylov expansion ratio (Int32, default 5)\nCUDENSITYMAT_OPERATOR_SPECTRUM_CONFIG_MAX_RESTARTS — max restarts (Int32, default 20)\nCUDENSITYMAT_OPERATOR_SPECTRUM_CONFIG_MIN_BLOCK_SIZE — min block size (Int32, default 1)\nvalue: Int32 configuration value\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create-Tuple{}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create","text":"create() -> cudensitymatHandle_t\n\nCreate a CuDensityMat library context handle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_elementary_operator-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, CUDA.CuArray{T}}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_elementary_operator","text":"create_elementary_operator(ws, space_mode_extents, data::CuArray{T};\n    sparsity=:none, diagonal_offsets=Int32[],\n    tensor_callback=nothing, tensor_gradient_callback=nothing) -> ElementaryOperator\n\nCreate a dense or multidiagonal elementary operator for a single mode.\n\nArguments\n\nws::WorkStream: Execution context\nspace_mode_extents::Vector{Int}: Dimensions of the space modes (e.g., [d] for single qudit)\ndata::CuArray{T}: Operator data on GPU (column-major)\nsparsity: :none for dense, :multidiagonal for sparse\ndiagonal_offsets: Required for multidiagonal sparsity\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_elementary_operator_batch-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, CUDA.CuArray{T}, Integer}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_elementary_operator_batch","text":"create_elementary_operator_batch(ws, space_mode_extents, data::CuArray{T}, batch_size;\n    kwargs...) -> ElementaryOperator\n\nCreate a batched elementary operator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_expectation-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_expectation","text":"create_expectation(ws, operator) -> Expectation\n\nCreate an expectation value descriptor for the given operator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_matrix_operator-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, CUDA.CuArray{T}}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_matrix_operator","text":"create_matrix_operator(ws, space_mode_extents, data::CuArray{T};\n    tensor_callback=nothing, tensor_gradient_callback=nothing) -> MatrixOperator\n\nCreate a dense local matrix operator covering the full Hilbert space.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_matrix_operator_batch-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, AbstractVector{<:Integer}, CUDA.CuArray{T}, Integer}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_matrix_operator_batch","text":"create_matrix_operator_batch(ws, space_mode_extents, data::CuArray{T}, batch_size;\n    kwargs...) -> MatrixOperator\n\nCreate a batched dense local matrix operator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_operator-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_operator","text":"create_operator(ws, hilbert_space_dims) -> Operator\n\nCreate an empty composite operator for the given Hilbert space.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_operator_action-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, Vector{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_operator_action","text":"create_operator_action(ws, operators::Vector{Operator}) -> OperatorAction\n\nCreate an operator action descriptor for multiple operators.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_operator_spectrum-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_operator_spectrum","text":"create_operator_spectrum(ws, operator;\n    is_hermitian=true,\n    spectrum_kind=CUDENSITYMAT_OPERATOR_SPECTRUM_LARGEST) -> OperatorSpectrum\n\nCreate an eigenspectrum solver for the given operator.\n\nArguments\n\nis_hermitian: Whether the operator is Hermitian (enables optimized solver)\nspectrum_kind: Which eigenvalues to compute:\nCUDENSITYMAT_OPERATOR_SPECTRUM_LARGEST — largest by magnitude\nCUDENSITYMAT_OPERATOR_SPECTRUM_SMALLEST — smallest by magnitude\nCUDENSITYMAT_OPERATOR_SPECTRUM_LARGEST_REAL — largest real part\nCUDENSITYMAT_OPERATOR_SPECTRUM_SMALLEST_REAL — smallest real part\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_operator_term-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_operator_term","text":"create_operator_term(ws, hilbert_space_dims) -> OperatorTerm\n\nCreate an empty operator term for the given Hilbert space dimensions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_workspace-Tuple{Ptr{Nothing}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.create_workspace","text":"create_workspace(handle) -> cudensitymatWorkspaceDescriptor_t\n\nCreate a workspace descriptor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.destroy-Tuple{Ptr{Nothing}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.destroy","text":"destroy(handle::cudensitymatHandle_t)\n\nDestroy a CuDensityMat library context handle.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.destroy_workspace-Tuple{Ptr{Nothing}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.destroy_workspace","text":"destroy_workspace(workspace)\n\nDestroy a workspace descriptor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.get_num_ranks-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.get_num_ranks","text":"get_num_ranks(ws::WorkStream) -> Int\n\nReturn the number of distributed processes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.get_proc_rank-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.get_proc_rank","text":"get_proc_rank(ws::WorkStream) -> Int\n\nReturn the rank of the current process.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.handle-Tuple{}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.handle","text":"handle() -> cudensitymatHandle_t\n\nGet a cuDensityMat library handle for the current CUDA context. Handles are cached per-context and reused.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.initialize_zero!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.initialize_zero!","text":"initialize_zero!(state)\n\nSet all elements of the state to zero using the C API.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.inner_product-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}, Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.inner_product","text":"inner_product(left, right) -> Vector{T}\n\nCompute inner product(s) ⟨left|right⟩. Returns a CPU vector of length batch_size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.inplace_accumulate!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}, Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}}, Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}, Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}, Any}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.inplace_accumulate!","text":"inplace_accumulate!(dest, src, factors=1)\n\nAccumulate: dest += factors * src. Both states must be compatible.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.inplace_scale!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}, Any}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.inplace_scale!","text":"inplace_scale!(state, factors)\n\nScale the state by scalar factor(s).\n\nfactors can be a scalar, a Vector, or a CuVector of length batch_size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.local_info-Union{Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.local_info","text":"local_info(state) -> (shape::Tuple, offsets::Tuple)\n\nLocal storage buffer dimensions and mode offsets. The last dimension is always the batch dimension.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.norm-Union{Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.norm","text":"norm(state) -> Vector{real(T)}\n\nCompute the squared Frobenius norm(s). Returns a CPU vector of length batch_size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.num_components-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.num_components","text":"num_components(state) -> Int\n\nNumber of storage components (1 for single-GPU, >1 for distributed).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_action!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorAction, AbstractVector{<:CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_action!","text":"prepare_action!(ws, action, states_in, state_out;\n    compute_type=CUDENSITYMAT_COMPUTE_64F, workspace_limit=nothing)\n\nPrepare the operator action computation (one-time setup).\n\nIf workspace_limit is nothing (default), uses 80% of free GPU memory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_expectation!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Expectation, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_expectation!","text":"prepare_expectation!(ws, expectation, state;\n    compute_type=CUDENSITYMAT_COMPUTE_64F, workspace_limit=nothing)\n\nPrepare expectation value computation (one-time setup).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_operator_action!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_operator_action!","text":"prepare_operator_action!(ws, operator, state_in, state_out;\n    compute_type=CUDENSITYMAT_COMPUTE_64F, workspace_limit=nothing)\n\nPrepare single-operator action computation.\n\nIf workspace_limit is nothing (default), uses 80% of free GPU memory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_operator_action_backward!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.Operator, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_operator_action_backward!","text":"prepare_operator_action_backward!(ws, operator, state_in, state_out_adj;\n    compute_type=CUDENSITYMAT_COMPUTE_64F, workspace_limit=nothing)\n\nPrepare backward differentiation of a single-operator action.\n\nArguments\n\nstate_in: The forward-pass input state\nstate_out_adj: The adjoint of the forward-pass output state (∂L/∂state_out)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_spectrum!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.OperatorSpectrum, Integer, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.AbstractState}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.prepare_spectrum!","text":"prepare_spectrum!(ws, spectrum, max_eigenstates, state;\n    compute_type=CUDENSITYMAT_COMPUTE_64F, workspace_limit=nothing)\n\nPrepare eigenspectrum computation.\n\nArguments\n\nmax_eigenstates: Maximum number of eigenvalues/eigenstates to compute\nstate: A template state (defines the Hilbert space structure)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.release_handle-Tuple{Ptr{Nothing}}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.release_handle","text":"release_handle(h::cudensitymatHandle_t)\n\nReturn a handle to the cache for reuse.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.release_workspace!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.release_workspace!","text":"release_workspace!(ws::WorkStream)\n\nRelease the workspace buffer and create a fresh workspace descriptor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.set_communicator!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, Symbol}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.set_communicator!","text":"set_communicator!(ws::WorkStream, provider::Symbol; comm_ptr=nothing, comm_size=nothing)\n\nConfigure distributed execution on the WorkStream.\n\nArguments\n\nprovider: :none, :mpi, or :nccl\ncomm_ptr: Pointer to the communicator (MPIComm* or ncclCommt*)\ncomm_size: Size of the communicator object in bytes\n\nMPI Example\n\nusing MPI\nMPI.Init()\ncomm = MPI.COMM_WORLD\nset_communicator!(ws, :mpi;\n    comm_ptr=MPI.API.MPI_Comm_c2f(comm),\n    comm_size=sizeof(MPI.MPI_Comm))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.set_random_seed!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, Integer}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.set_random_seed!","text":"set_random_seed!(ws::WorkStream, seed::Integer)\n\nReset the random seed used by the library's internal random number generator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.state_view-Union{Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.state_view","text":"state_view(state) -> CuArray\n\nReturn a multidimensional view of the state's storage buffer.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.storage_size-Union{Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.storage_size","text":"storage_size(state) -> Int\n\nStorage buffer size in number of elements of the state's data type.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.trace-Union{Tuple{Union{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DenseMixedState{T}, CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.DensePureState{T}}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.trace","text":"trace(state) -> Vector{T}\n\nCompute the trace(s). Returns a CPU vector of length batch_size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.unregister_callback!-Tuple{Any}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.unregister_callback!","text":"unregister_callback!(refs)\n\nRelease a callback from the global registry, allowing GC. Call this after destroying the operator that uses the callback.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.version-Tuple{}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.version","text":"version()\n\nReturn the CuDensityMat library version as a VersionNumber.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.workspace_allocate!-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream, Int64}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.workspace_allocate!","text":"workspace_allocate!(ws::WorkStream, size::Int; memspace=:device, kind=:scratch)\n\nAllocate and attach a workspace buffer of the given size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.workspace_query_size-Tuple{CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.WorkStream}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.workspace_query_size","text":"workspace_query_size(ws::WorkStream; memspace=:device, kind=:scratch) -> Int\n\nQuery the required workspace buffer size in bytes after a prepare call.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.wrap_scalar_callback-Tuple{Function}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.wrap_scalar_callback","text":"wrap_scalar_callback(f; gradient=nothing) -> (cb, gcb, refs)\n\nWrap a Julia function as a scalar callback for time-dependent coefficients.\n\nArguments\n\nf: Function with signature f(time::Float64, params::Matrix{Float64}, storage::Vector{T}) where T matches the operator's data type. params is (numParams, batchSize), storage is (batchSize,). Write the coefficient values into storage.\ngradient: Optional gradient function with signature g(time::Float64, params::Matrix{Float64}, scalar_grad::Vector{T}, params_grad::Matrix{Float64})\n\nReturns\n\ncb::cudensitymatWrappedScalarCallback_t — the callback struct\ngcb::cudensitymatWrappedScalarGradientCallback_t — the gradient callback struct\nrefs — opaque reference holder (keep alive while callback is in use)\n\nExample\n\n# Time-dependent coefficient: f(t) = exp(iΩt) where Ω = params[1,:]\nfunction my_coeff(time, params, storage)\n    for i in axes(storage, 1)\n        ω = params[1, i]\n        storage[i] = complex(cos(ω * time), sin(ω * time))\n    end\nend\n\ncb, gcb, refs = wrap_scalar_callback(my_coeff)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/cudensitymat/#CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.wrap_tensor_callback-Tuple{Function}","page":"CuDensityMat","title":"CuQuantum.CuDensityMat.wrap_tensor_callback","text":"wrap_tensor_callback(f; gradient=nothing) -> (cb, gcb, refs)\n\nWrap a Julia function as a tensor callback for time-dependent operator elements.\n\nArguments\n\nf: Function with signature f(time::Float64, params::Matrix{Float64}, storage::Array{T}) where storage shape is (d1, d2, ..., d1, d2, ..., batchSize) for dense operators. Write the tensor elements into storage.\ngradient: Optional gradient function.\n\nReturns\n\ncb::cudensitymatWrappedTensorCallback_t\ngcb::cudensitymatWrappedTensorGradientCallback_t\nrefs — opaque reference holder\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#CuQuantum.jl","page":"Home","title":"CuQuantum.jl","text":"Julia bindings for the NVIDIA cuQuantum SDK.\n\nCuQuantum.jl provides high-level Julia wrappers for NVIDIA's cuQuantum libraries, enabling GPU-accelerated quantum computing simulations. The current focus is on cuDensityMat — a high-performance library for density matrix simulation of open quantum systems.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Features","page":"Home","title":"Features","text":"Density matrix simulation — Lindblad master equation dynamics with time-dependent Hamiltonians\nTime-dependent operators — CPU callbacks for scalar coefficients and tensor elements\nBackward differentiation — parameter gradients for quantum optimal control (single-GPU)\nExpectation values — textTr(O rho) for arbitrary operators\nEigenspectrum — extreme eigenvalues of many-body operators\nMPI/NCCL distributed — multi-GPU forward-pass computation\nTensor network contraction — operators are never materialized as full superoperator matrices, enabling simulation of systems too large for sparse matrix approaches","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quick-Example","page":"Home","title":"Quick Example","text":"using CuQuantum\nusing CuQuantum.CuDensityMat\nusing CUDA\n\n# Create a workspace (manages GPU handle, workspace memory, CUDA stream)\nws = WorkStream()\n\n# Define a 2-cavity system with Fock truncation d=3\ndims = [3, 3]\n\n# Build a sigma_z operator on the first cavity\nσz_data = CUDA.CuVector{ComplexF64}([1, 0, 0, 0, -1, 0, 0, 0, 0])\nelem = create_elementary_operator(ws, [3], σz_data)\n\n# Assemble into a full operator term\nterm = create_operator_term(ws, dims)\nappend_elementary_product!(term, [elem], Int32[0], Int32[0])\n\n# Build the composite operator\noperator = create_operator(ws, dims)\nappend_term!(operator, term; duality=0, coefficient=ComplexF64(0, -1))  # -iHρ\nappend_term!(operator, term; duality=1, coefficient=ComplexF64(0, +1))  # +iρH\n\n# Create input/output density matrices\nρ_in = DenseMixedState{ComplexF64}(ws, (3, 3); batch_size=1)\nρ_out = DenseMixedState{ComplexF64}(ws, (3, 3); batch_size=1)\nallocate_storage!(ρ_in)\nallocate_storage!(ρ_out)\n\n# Prepare and compute the action: ρ_out = L[ρ_in]\nprepare_operator_action!(ws, operator, ρ_in, ρ_out)\ninitialize_zero!(ρ_out)\ncompute_operator_action!(ws, operator, ρ_in, ρ_out; time=0.0, batch_size=1)\n\nclose(ws)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Supported-Hardware","page":"Home","title":"Supported Hardware","text":"GPU architectures: Turing, Ampere, Ada, Hopper, Blackwell\nOS: Linux (x86_64, ARM64)\nCUDA Toolkit: 12.x or 13.x","category":"section"},{"location":"#Package-Status","page":"Home","title":"Package Status","text":"Component Status\ncuDensityMat Fully wrapped (58 C API functions)\ncuStateVec Planned\ncuTensorNet Planned\ncuPauliProp Planned\ncuStabilizer Planned","category":"section"},{"location":"#Related-Resources","page":"Home","title":"Related Resources","text":"NVIDIA cuQuantum SDK documentation\ncuDensityMat API reference\ncuDensityMat C++ examples\nPiccolo.jl — quantum optimal control built on CuQuantum.jl","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#Quantum-States","page":"States","title":"Quantum States","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#State-Types","page":"States","title":"State Types","text":"CuQuantum.jl provides two state types, both stored as dense tensors on the GPU:","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#DensePureState{T}","page":"States","title":"DensePureState{T}","text":"A pure quantum state psirangle stored as a rank-M tensor with shape (d_1 d_2 ldots d_M).\n\n# 2-qubit pure state (d₁=2, d₂=2)\nψ = DensePureState{ComplexF64}(ws, (2, 2); batch_size=1)\nallocate_storage!(ψ)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#DenseMixedState{T}","page":"States","title":"DenseMixedState{T}","text":"A density matrix rho stored as a rank-2M tensor with shape (d_1 ldots d_M d_1 ldots d_M), where the first M indices are ket (row) and the last M are bra (column).\n\n# 2-cavity mixed state (d₁=3, d₂=3), density matrix is 9×9\nρ = DenseMixedState{ComplexF64}(ws, (3, 3); batch_size=1)\nallocate_storage!(ρ)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#Supported-Data-Types","page":"States","title":"Supported Data Types","text":"ComplexF64 — double precision (recommended)\nComplexF32 — single precision (faster, less accurate)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#State-Operations","page":"States","title":"State Operations","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#Initialization","page":"States","title":"Initialization","text":"# Zero-initialize (via cuDensityMat C API)\ninitialize_zero!(state)\n\n# Copy data from CPU\nrho_cpu = zeros(ComplexF64, 9 * 9)\nrho_cpu[1] = 1.0  # |0,0⟩⟨0,0|\ncopyto!(ρ.storage, CUDA.CuVector{ComplexF64}(rho_cpu))","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#Linear-Algebra","page":"States","title":"Linear Algebra","text":"# Scale: ρ ← α * ρ\ninplace_scale!(ρ, ComplexF64(0.5))\n\n# Accumulate: ρ_dest ← ρ_dest + α * ρ_src\ninplace_accumulate!(ρ_dest, ρ_src, ComplexF64(dt))\n\n# Trace: Tr(ρ)\ntr = trace(ρ)  # returns Vector{ComplexF64} of length batch_size\n\n# Norm: ||ρ||²_F (squared Frobenius norm)\nn = norm(ρ)  # returns Vector{Float64}\n\n# Inner product: ⟨ρ_left | ρ_right⟩\nip = inner_product(ρ_left, ρ_right)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#Batched-States","page":"States","title":"Batched States","text":"All state types support batched operations — multiple independent states processed in parallel:\n\n# 16 density matrices in parallel\nρ_batch = DenseMixedState{ComplexF64}(ws, (3, 3); batch_size=16)\nallocate_storage!(ρ_batch)\n\nThe batch dimension is the last index in storage. All compute functions (trace, norm, compute_operator_action!, etc.) operate on all batch members simultaneously.","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/states/#Memory-Management","page":"States","title":"Memory Management","text":"State storage is allocated on the GPU via allocate_storage!. The GPU memory is released when the state is garbage collected, or when the WorkStream is closed.\n\nρ = DenseMixedState{ComplexF64}(ws, (3, 3); batch_size=1)\nallocate_storage!(ρ)  # allocates 9*9*16 = 1296 bytes on GPU\n# ... use ρ ...\nclose(ws)  # releases all associated GPU resources","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/overview/#Concepts-Overview","page":"Overview","title":"Concepts Overview","text":"CuQuantum.jl wraps the NVIDIA cuDensityMat library for GPU-accelerated density matrix simulation. This section explains the key concepts.","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/overview/#Architecture","page":"Overview","title":"Architecture","text":"The cuDensityMat library represents quantum operators as sums of tensor products of elementary operators. Instead of materializing the full Liouvillian superoperator as a matrix (which scales as d^2M times d^2M), it uses tensor network contraction to compute the action Lrho directly. This allows simulation of systems far too large for explicit matrix approaches.\n\nElementary Operators  →  Operator Terms  →  Operators  →  Operator Action\n    (single-mode)       (tensor products)   (sums of terms)   (L[ρ] computation)","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/overview/#Hilbert-Space","page":"Overview","title":"Hilbert Space","text":"The quantum system is defined as a tensor product of M modes, each with dimension d_m:\n\nmathcalH = bigotimes_m=1^M mathbbC^d_m\n\nFor example, M=4 cavities each truncated to d=3 Fock states gives a Hilbert space of dimension 3^4 = 81.","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/overview/#Density-Matrix","page":"Overview","title":"Density Matrix","text":"Density matrices rho are stored as dense tensors on the GPU:\n\nDensePureState: pure state psirangle with shape (d_1 d_2 ldots d_M)\nDenseMixedState: mixed state rho with shape (d_1 d_2 ldots d_M d_1 d_2 ldots d_M)\n\nBoth support batched operations (multiple states in parallel).","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/overview/#Lindblad-Master-Equation","page":"Overview","title":"Lindblad Master Equation","text":"The primary use case is the Lindblad master equation:\n\ndotrho = -iH(t) rho + sum_k gamma_k left( L_k rho L_k^dagger - frac12L_k^dagger L_k rho right)\n\nThis is decomposed into operator terms and assembled with appropriate duality flags:\n\nPhysical term Duality Coefficient\n-iHrho 0 (ket/left) -i\n+irho H 1 (bra/right) +i\ngamma Lrho L^dagger 0 (sandwich via fused op) gamma\n-fracgamma2 L^dagger L rho 0 (left) -gamma2\n-fracgamma2 rho L^dagger L 1 (right) -gamma2","category":"section"},{"location":"concepts/overview/#WorkStream","page":"Overview","title":"WorkStream","text":"The WorkStream is the central resource manager. It holds:\n\nA cuDensityMat library handle (GPU context)\nA workspace descriptor (scratch memory for contractions)\nA CUDA stream for asynchronous execution\nAn optional MPI/NCCL communicator for distributed computation","category":"section"}]
}
